The cardinals of the Ċrizzaz tower have emerged from their seclusion. As white smoke leaves the top of the tower, a crowd start to gather outside. The announcement is made, the cardinals have chosen YOU to be the new Head Shaman of the Mnazubisti.

 

"Your mind is a temple" as the Mnazubisti say. Their fables of Fwammum burning his cakes and Nuġġuġuż oversleeping and missing the battle are used as stark reminders of how insobriety leads to the wrath of the Gods. Therefore, it should not surprise us to learm that the consumption of wine and beer is largely unheard of amongst the Mnazubisti. Some even refuse to enjoy music and poetry fearing a corruption of their God-given faculty of reason. As they like to say "Do not squander the gift of the Gods".

Your people consume 75% less Wine and 100% less Beer.

 

The Mnazubisti belive that we are all a violent collection of fumes, forcibly combined at birth to atone for our existential guilt. The Mnazubisti worship their ancestors' ashes, which are stored in large green clay pots, called Drabuk. The Drabuk are filled in Mnazubisti funerals where the deceased is burned a big bonfire. The burning process, it is believed, releases the fumes and helps to restore balance to the world. They worship death as the final and most cruical stage in life, but not an end to it, as they always keep their ancestors nearby to continue their legacy and seek their advice. 

Your people consume 50% more Pottery.

 

The day of the Qudrur is the most highly anticipated feast in the Mnazubisti calendar. The Toweħ, a firm, hand-sized, red fruit is harvested then bought in large bags by the Mnazubisti. On the day before Qudrur, believers spend their time constructing shields and armour out of sticks and straw and form into teams of twenty-seven each. At dawn, a horn is sounded and the teams attempt to fight their way into each other's camps throwing Toweħ at their opponents as they go.  In the middle of every camp is a red flag, the team that collects the most flags before the horm is blown at dusk is declared the winner and is immortalised in the temple's hall of fame.   

Your people consume 75% more Fruit.

 

Guide your people to prosperity. Go forth into the world.
Welcome, Atalaster. Leader of the Mnazubisti.

The cardinals of the Spomous tower have emerged from their seclusion. As purple smoke leaves the top of the tower, a crowd starts to gather outside. The announcement is made, the cardinals have chosen YOU to be the new Pope of the Srartous Truthers.

 

The Srartous Truthers splintered off from the Hanos, after the latter tried to force the people to pay for the construction of yet another opulent temple to Hafos. Tired of being taxed by a corrupt clergy, the Srartous Truthers insisted that spiritual richness must be distinct from physical richness. Now fully separated from the Hanos, Srartous Truthers holy men take vows of poverty and their temples are simple unornate structures which look like storehouses compared to the ornate marble temples of the Hanos.

Your people consume 75% less Marble.

 

For the Srartous Truthers, the innocence of youth is sacred. All beings are born pure, but as time goes by, the evil world tarnishes and ages the body.  Sinning accelerates this process greatly with the greatest and final sin, despair, leading to death. On the anniversery of the birth of a member of the Srartous Truthers, a big party is thrown to mourn the passage of time and celebrate the person's achievments. The death of someone at a young age is an unbearable tragedy to the Srartous Truthers, and the sanctity of youth must be respected for all living things. Most believers will avoid eating eggs, which symbolise the pure embryo, some even avoiding fish, being unable to determine if they are old enough. 

Your people consume 25% less Fish and 75% less Egg.

 

"And thus spoke Rottus", begins the Spapus, holiest book for the Srartous Truthers. They believe that Rottus, inspired directly by God, spoke 142 sayings that were recored in the Spapus. Copies of the Spapus have been handed down and copied and re-copied for generations, it's archaic language spells out the principles of common decency on which the Srartous Truthers base themselves. Be sure that every believer has a blue-bound book closeby.

Your people consume 50% more Paper and 25% more Leather.

 

Guide your people to prosperity. Go forth into the world.
Welcome, Atalaster. Leader of the Srartous Truthers.
